title: For Trade:  Ruger Charger w.Accessories New, Never Fired!
postcontent:
Hello,



I am looking to trade my never-fired, Ruger Charger for a .22lr target pistol, preferably a Ruger Mark II or Mark III. I will also consider a Browning Buckmark.



The Ruger Charger has never been fired, and is the stainless & light grey finish. It comes with a brand new Truglow red/green dot sight (cost $100.00) with five reticles in each color, and adjustable brightness. There is also one factory 10-round magazine, a Pro-Mag 32-round magazine (steel-lipped), the original box, all original paperwork, locks, the bipod, and nice carry bag with the Ruger logo.

This pistol is very clean, with no issues. The only reason I am looking to trade for a target pistol is that I can better teach my youngster to shoot with something that can actually be handled and fired in hand. The Charger can only be fired from a bench rest position by my boy, and offers little in the way of teaching grip or stance. The reach from the grip to trigger on the Charger is also a bit long for him as well.



That said, I am looking primarily for a Ruger Mark II or Mark III with bull barrel. I will also consider a 22/45 if it has the replaceable grips. A Browning Buckmark will also be considered, as will other makes and models of target pistol in .22lr. Just contact me to let me know what you have and we'll think about it.



I may consider other arms as well, such as a decent 22lr rifle, a 12ga with a rear sight (ramp, ghost ring, etc.). Prefer tactical style shotgun over hunting style. I am not opposed to buying my son a target pistol if I work out another deal on something else here, so again, feel free to contact me with any fair offer. Also feel free to ask for any further details or for more pictures.
Will meet to trade face to face (will deal trade via FFL as well if necessary), and will require a signed and certified bill of sale, as well as ID info. as proof of state residence.

title: For Sale:  NEW LaRue Tactical 16 inch Predatobr 5.56
postcontent:
I have for sale a new Larue Tactical Predatobr in the 5.56 caliber.  Please email me if you have any questions.  Thank you.

LaRue Tactical PredatOBR™ 5.56 
The PredatOBR 5.56 was designed for those who are searching for a hybrid cross between the standard OBR and PredatAR 5.56x45 Rifles. The PredatOBR takes the highly accurate OBR 5.56 design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least-possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for. 

The most remarkable feature of the PredatOBR is its ability to be completely “broken down” and stored into the supplied Roll-Bag and Tool Box. The PredatOBR handguard has a locking stainless steel QD Lever system on each side. Once the levers are released, the handguard slides off of the upper assembly in seconds. The PredatOBR's barrel can easily be removed with the supplied PredatOBR Barrel Wrench, unscrew the Barrel Nut from Receiver and pull the Barrel Assembly free from Receiver. No need to remove the gas tube, gas block or muzzle device. Reverse the process to reinstall. Hand-tighten Barrel Nut and torque approximately 1/8-turn past hand-tight (Approximately 40-50 foot pounds). Once reassembled correctly, the point of impact (POI) shift will be 0.0 to 0.5 MOA of the original.

PredatOBR barrels are chambered in 5.56x45mm, and feature rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All muzzles are threaded in 1/2 x 28. Like the OBR and PredatAR riles, LaRue has eliminated the conventional AR barrel nut and bolt the handguard directly to the proprietary upper receiver, creating a true “free-float” barrel. The handguard does not touch the barrel or barrel nut at any place. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet aluminum for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though it has been lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy. 

The PredatOBR has threaded stainless-steel hard-points over the entire length of the handguard at the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock positions. These hard-points have an integral spine built-in for structural support. Provided with the system are three 3-inch MIL-STD-1913 rail sections that can be positioned anywhere along the handguard, per operator preference. These rail sections are attachable/detachable using a supplied tool (Torx® T-15 wrench). The rail sections are CNC-machined from billet aluminum. This robust solution provides a perfect precision mounting space for aiming lasers, illumination and bipods.

The PredatOBR's Port Selector Technology™ (PST) gas block is adjustable, to aid in the optimum function when using a sound suppressor. This special gas block contains a dual port mechanism that is operated by rotating a lever from one side to another. When the lever is rotated to the right-side of the rifle, the gasses are reduced, to compensate for the extra blowback created by the suppressor. When rotated to the left side, the gasses are increased for use without a suppressor.

The LaRue Tactical 6-position Retract Action Trigger (R.A.T.) Stock comes standard with every PredatOBR. It is ergonomic, has protected control surfaces and contains a set of cleaning rods in an internal compartment. Since the height of the 12 o’clock rail is at the optimum position, there is no need for a cheek riser as part of this system. The New A-PEG grip also comes standard. This grip was designed to be ambidextrous and places the hand in the corrected position for precision shooting.


Specifications:
Caliber: 5.56 x 45 mm NATO 
Barrel Lengths: 14.5”,16.1”and 18” 
Rifling Twist Rate: 1/8
Barrel Life: 10,000 (approx) 
Gas System: Direct Impingement with LaRue PST™ port selector 

Accessories: 
2ea, 30-Round Magazines
3ea 3” Rail Sections
Operators Manual
Carrying Case “Toolbox”
Roll-Up Cloth Case
Barrel Wrench

title: For Sale:  Taurus PT-92 with extras
postcontent:
$400 OBO

For sale by private owner, Taurus PT-92AF 9mm pistol. This is a 1988 production DA/SA model with manual safety only, no decocker. Included with the pistol is one OEM 15 rd magazine, one 18 round Mec-Gar magazine, which is very high quality. Pistol comes with one set pachmayr grips, soft rubber with checkering, and one set hogue smooth exotic hardwood grips. I also have a blackhawk SERPA retention hostler for a Beretta M9, which required slight modification to the retention tab to fit the slightly different trigger guard of the Taurus variant. 

I have owned this pistol for 5 years and have no issues with it. Makes a great firearm for personal defense or recreation. Pistol is very comfortable and naturally easy to point and shoot. 9mm recoil is very mild and easy to manage, especially with the soft rubber Pachmayr grips.  I am only selling to free up money and safe space for a new firearm. 

A little history of the Taurus 92 pistol. Taurus 92 bought the Brazilian Beretta factory lock stock and barrel and began producing their clones using the same exact machinery and specifications. The taurus will often fit hostlers made for the beretta m9, but the trigger guards are slightly different in shape and certain holsters may or may not be compatible. Beretta and taurus magazines are not interchangeable, but good quality mags are available for comparable prices, such as from Mec Gar. Another difference is the location of the manual safety. Unlike the Beretta awkward slide mounted safety, Taurus manual safeties are located on the frame, and are consistent with most other DA/SA pistols available.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Taurus PT 24/7 OSS DS .45
postcontent:
Dessert Tan, very rare .45 Taurus. (Flashlight NOT included)
This was a model designed for the US Military in 2006 when the SOCOM division put out request for a new side arm for their operators. The funding was scrapped by the government but the gun was still made. This is the result. One of the smoothest guns I've fired. comparable to my Glock 22 .40 

The gun shows some holster & light mounting wear. Functions great. Personally put 25 rounds through it. Unknown what previous owner put through. 

This gun is almost impossible to find in dessert tan.

Comes with 2 factory Taurus mags 10 & 12 round
and two generic mags. Also comes with generic nylon holster. 

Will trade for Glock 19, 23 or 26

918 six three eight 9868

title: For Sale/Trade:  Chinese Military  T53 Mosin Carbine 7.62x54  Cal.
postcontent:
This is the exact copy of the Russian M44 with internal 5 round magazine.  This comes
with a bolt-on muzzle break and Chinese military dog leash style straps,  20 inch barrel   On the front of this carbine is the crucifix style retractable bayonet that is really neat.  Russia turned over the production of the M44 to the Chinese and this one survived.  It is from the Jianshe Arsenal,  factory 296,  made in 1955.  The readily available 7.62x54 ammo is inexpensive and this will be a lot of fun with Spring coming up.

title: For Sale:  H&K USP 45 Special Forces Weapon of Choice NIB
postcontent:
Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. In stock and ready for delivery, call Rick at REDACTED.
